President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in Guam due to Typhoon Mangkhut and has ordered federal assistance to support recovery efforts. Federal funding will be provided on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, facility repairs, and hazard mitigation measures. Benigno Bern Ruiz has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made based on damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.